  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<blockquote><p>Prerequisite: Level 2+ Warlock</p></blockquote><p>As a Magic action, a creature of your choice that you can see within 60 feet must make a Charisma saving throw. For the next minute, whenever a target that fails this saving throw makes an attack roll or a saving throw, the target must roll a d4 and subtract the number rolled from the attack roll or saving throw.</p><p>The affected creature can repeat the saving throw once per turn, only if it rolls a 1 on the d4 before the start of it's next turn, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p><p>At level 7 in Warlock, as long as one creature within 60 feet of you is affected by your Thief of Five Fates, you can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to your attack rolls and saving throws.</p><p><strong>Beam Replacement.</strong> This may be invoked in place of one of your Eldritch Blast beams.</p>",
